benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/admin/cache/accounts/{accountId} - Invalidates Caches per account level

covered: Backward compatibility with previous endpoint usage (TC19)
gaps: Pagination behavior for large datasets is not covered
Authorization authorization beyond 401 (e.g., 403) is not explicitly tested
Rate limiting/throttling scenarios are not tested
Caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and caching behavior validation are not tested
Internal server error scenarios (e.g., 500) are not simulated
Explicit soft-delete behavior or audit/logging validations are not tested
recommendations: Add tests for pagination handling if the delete operation can affect large numbers of accounts or if listing is involved, ensuring correct behavior with large datasets.
Add tests for authorization beyond basic admin authentication (e.g., 403 Forbidden for insufficient permissions).
Introduce rate limiting/throttling tests to validate concurrent requests do not overwhelm the system and proper error handling occurs.
Include scenarios validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and caching behavior on DELETE responses if applicable.
Add test cases simulating internal server errors (500) to verify graceful degradation and proper error messaging.
Consider explicit soft-delete/audit verification if the system marks deletes without permanent removal and logs the action.
